FBIS3-31935 "drlat020_g_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Jan 1994 Guatemala Army Blames URNG for Recent Terrorist Actions PA2901024994 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in Spanish 0000 GMT 29 Jan 94 PA2901024994 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "News Patrol" newscast] [Text] Army spokeswoman Major Berta Vargas de Marroquin blamed URNG [Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity] guerrillas for the recent terrorist actions because it was URNG members who planted the powerful bombs on electricity pylons located throughout Guatemala City at 2100. She pointed out that these bombs caused blackouts and left people without lights. Vargas de Marroquin noted that, by perpetrating these criminal actions, URNG members endanger the physical safety of the population, destroy the country's infrastructure, hurt private citizens by depriving them of indispensable electrical power, and cause considerable financial losses to the industrial sector and the population in general.
